386→                        <div id="content">Determine the Ramsey number\[R(C_4,S_n),\]where $S_n=K_{1,n}$ is the star on $n+1$ vertices.<br><br>In particular, is it true that, for any $c&#62;0$, there are infinitely many $n$ such that\[R(C_4,S_n)\leq n+\sqrt{n}-c?\]</div>
387→                        <div id="problem_id"><a href="/552">#552</a>: <a href="#cite-BEFRS89-552" onclick="event.preventDefault();addNewBox('BEFRS89','552'); return false;">[BEFRS89]</a><a href="#cite-Er93-552" onclick="event.preventDefault();addNewBox('Er93','552'); return false;">[Er93,p.345]</a><a href="#cite-Er94b-552" onclick="event.preventDefault();addNewBox('Er94b','552'); return false;">[Er94b]</a><a href="#cite-Er95-552" onclick="event.preventDefault();addNewBox('Er95','552'); return false;">[Er95]</a><a href="#cite-Er96-552" onclick="event.preventDefault();addNewBox('Er96','552'); return false;">[Er96]</a></div>
